Pancreatic pseudocysts: apropos of a case of pancreatitis and the puerperium. A 26 years old white patient with diagnosis of a pancreatitis and pancreatic pseudocyst during the puerperium is reported. Among the most important diagnostic procedure we have used are the endoscopy, Rx and TC. Cholecystectomy showed many small stones. Gastrocystostomy was done. Pancreatitis is as often in multiparous patients as in primipara. Near the 80% of the cases appear during the third term of pregnancy and puerperium. Many etiologycal factor play a role in the development of this disease, cholelithiasis being 65% of them. Mother-faetal mortality is near 20%.